Raising Crops
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0064]
To grow crops, first you must till the land with a Hoe.
Equip a Hoe and press the Tool Button.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0065]
Land with objects on it can't be tilled. To clear the
ground, cut Weeds with a Sickle, or pull them by pressing
the Confirm Button.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0066]
Equip a Hammer to crush Stones and an Axe to cut
Branches. Smaller debris can also be cleared by
picking up and moving them.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0067]
Boulders and Stumps cannot be moved by hand. These can
be broken with tools upgraded at the Forge.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0068]
Once the land has been tilled, use a seed bag on it to plant
seeds. Ground that hasn't been tilled cannot be seeded.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0069]
Once the seeds have been planted, the next step is to
water them using a Watering Can.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0070]
To use a Watering Can, first it must be filled with water.
Stand next to a water source and equip the Watering
Can to fill it.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0071]
Water your fields once a day for several days to grow
your crops. Keep watering them every day until they're
ripe.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0072]
Some crops can only be raised during certain seasons.
The General Store will sell seeds in their proper season.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0073]
Be careful! If you plant seeds out of season,
they won't grow.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0074]
Some types of crops are "vine crops." These crops
produce multiple yields, and once harvested can be
watered again to grow more.
