Raising Chickens
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0169]
When raising chickens be sure to feed them every day.
Collect Chicken/Rabbit Feed from the Dispenser and put
it in a Feeding Bin.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0170]
Put enough Feed in the Feeding Bins for each chicken.
If you forget to feed them, they won't grow or lay Eggs.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0171]
You can also give your chickens their Feed directly.
It's important to show your animals love and care
as you raise them.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0172]
Stand near a chicken and press the Confirm Button
to talk to them.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0173]
As long as your chickens are properly fed they will lay
one Egg a day.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0174]
And the more the chicken likes you, the better the quality
that Egg will be.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0175]
Put an Egg in the Incubator and in a few days it will
hatch into a chick.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0176]
Chicks born on your farm will grow to like you more
quickly than chickens that are bought.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0177]
Ring the Bell outside your Coop to send your chickens out
to pasture.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0178]
Leave them in the pasture for several hours and they will
find their own food, so you won't need to feed them.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0179]
At 8:00 PM, chickens out in the pasture will
automatically return to the Coop.
