[0462]
The Fetch Fest
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0463]
Throw the Disc for your pet to catch! Adjust the
distance and try to throw it as far as your pet can reach.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0464]
When the game begins, the cursor will start to move.
Press the Confirm Button at just the right time to
stop it.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0465]
The green section of the "throw gauge" is your pet's
catching range. Though even then, it's not a guarantee
that they will catch the Disc.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0466]
The red part of the gauge is too far for your pet to
catch the Disc.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0467]
Try to pick just the right spot on the green part of the
gauge, and throw the Disc as far as your pet can catch.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0468]
You can practice throwing the Disc with your pet to
increase the range in which they can catch it.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0469]
But if you play too many times in one day, your pet
will get bored and they won't want to play any more
that day.
<------------------------------------------------------->
[0470]
The more your pet likes you, the more often they will
want to play in a day.
